ltants search Stop smoking services Urgent care services All directories You are here: The NHS in England Healthcare abroad Cover your healthcare abroad Whatever your reasons for going abroad, you may be entitled to medical care at reduced cost or sometimes free. Your entitlement will vary based on whether you're going to an European Economic Area country (EEA) or elsewhere in the world. Free EHIC If you're going abroad on holiday or a business trip, you should apply for a free European Health Insurance Card (EHIC), which may give you access to reduced-cost medical treatment.  About the EHIC Apply for an EHIC Treatment in Europe Find out what your funding options are if you wish to have treatment in Europe and how to apply for it. Getting started Funding options Giving birth Checklist Moving abroad Find out if you are still eligible for healthcare paid by the UK when you're going to live, work or study in another EEA country. Living abroad Studying abroad   Country guides Use the country-by-country guide and find out if you are entitled to healthcare paid by the UK. Different rules apply depending on the circumstances of your visit.  EEA countries Non-EEA countries Visiting England Find out how to access NHS services during your visit in England and check under what circumstances you are exempt from charges. EEA visitors Non-EEA visitors Visitors' FAQ  Moving to England Find out how to access NHS services if you are moving to England. Moving from the EEA Moving from outside the EEA Travel tips Get practical advice on sun safety, preventing malaria, travel insurance, DVT, jet lag and more. Before you travel Travel health check list Food and water abroad Travel FAQs Travel vaccinations Learn about the vaccinations available for travellers, and the diseases they protect against. Available jabs Travel jabs by destination Travel jabs on the NHS  Page last reviewed: 17\/08\/2015 Next review due: 17\/08\/2017 Apply for a free EHIC  The EHIC is entirely free of charge. However, other, unofficial, websites may charge you if you apply through them. Apply now for your free EHIC. For general queries about the EHIC, or if you're having difficulties with the online application form, updating your personal details, or replacing a lost or stolen card, call the automated EHIC application service on 0300 330 1350 (the line is manned from Monday to Friday 8am to 6pm and Saturday 9am to 3pm. A voice automated service is  available 24\/7). If you wish to claim a refund, call the Overseas Healthcare Team on 0191 218 1999. If calling from abroad ring +44 191 218 1999. EHIC on Facebook Follow EHIC on Facebook for the latest updates and answers to your questions European Health Insurance Card (EHIC): hot summer holidays Please enable JavaScript in order to view the video. Always expect the unexpected: a painful lesson the young man in this video had to learn. Find out why you should have a European Health Insurance Card (EHIC) when you go abroad. Media last reviewed: 17\/02\/2015 Next review due: 17\/02\/2017 Also on NHS Choices Altitude sickness Healthy holidays Insect bites Motion sickness Safe swimming: what's lurking in the water? Stings from marine creatures Sun screen and sun safety NHS Choices information Choices e-newsletters Your pages Site policies Terms and conditions Editorial policy Comments policy Syndication Privacy policy Cookies policy Links policy Accessibility Sitemap Other NHS sites Summary Care Records NHS Scotland NHS Northern Ireland NHS Wales NHS Jobs Health Careers Department of Health NHS England About the NHS The NHS in England About NHS services NHS Friends and Family Test Quality accounts NHS e-Referral Service Find authorities and trusts Healthwatch England The NHS complaints procedure Other channels Follow us on Twitter Facebook YouTube Video library Links library Other Languages Visit our language section for more health websites in foreign languages. Contact NHS Choices Choices helpdesk Freedom of Information requests 