afety Protect your skin against sun damage (including sunbeds) and reduce your risk of skin cancer. 12 UK insects and bugs that bite or sting The creatures that are most likely to feast on you, including wasps, bees, ants, spiders, midges and ticks. Safer sex on holiday Protect yourself from a sexually transmitted infection or unplanned pregnancy on holiday. Safe swimming: what's lurking in the water? How to make sure you don\u2019t catch or encounter anything nasty in the sea, river, pond or lake. Weather and hay fever The sun, rain and seasons all affect how much pollen is in the air and how bad your hay fever symptoms are. Summer feet tips Summer means sandals, so make sure your feet are attractive and in tip-top condition before baring them to the world. Plant dangers in the garden and countryside A guide to the plants that can sting, scratch or poison you and what to do if you or your family are affected. Stay gas safe this summer From boilers to barbecues, what you need to know about carbon monoxide poisoning. Getting started Protect yourself in the sun Get trained in first aid Become active (without joining a gym) Read guidelines on leisure safety Services near you Find addresses, phone numbers and websites for services near you Find and compare services Services Urgent Care Accident and emergency services Sexual health information and support Location Looking for other services? View services A-Z Also on NHS Choices Dehydration Food poisoning Hay fever Sexually transmitted infections Skin cancer JavaScript and the Flash Player are required to view NHS Choices tools. JavaScript can be switched on through your browser options. If you do not have a version of the Flash Player you can download the free Adobe Flash Player from Adobe Systems Incorporated. Media last reviewed: 22\/06\/2015 Next review due: 22\/06\/2017 Beach safety To make the most of your time at the seaside, be informed about the dangers and follow these simple safety tips Travel health Advice fo